<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
<p>When calling <code>choco list -lo</code>, add <code>--audit</code> to see information on who installed and when.</p>
<h3 id="requirements">Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>Chocolatey (<code>chocolatey</code> package) v0.10.7+.</li>
<li>Chocolatey for Business (C4B) Edition.</li>
<li>Chocolatey Licensed Extension (<code>chocolatey.extension</code> package) v1.12.0+.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="see-it-in-action">See It In Action</h2>
<p><img src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/docs/features/features_package_audit.png")" alt="Package Audit - if you are on https://chocolatey.org/docs/features-package-audit, see commented html below for detailed description of image" /></p>
<p>When shown, the user and domain are for the user who actually performed the installation. The &quot;Original User&quot; is the user who requested the install (outside of <a href="@Url.RouteUrl(RouteName.Docs, new { docName = "features-agent-service" })">Self-Service</a>, it would be the same as the installing user). The Installation Date and Time are in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601">ISO 8601</a> UTC time.</p>
